k\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 14, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104xbg1665702534713.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xbg1665702534713.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xbg1665702534713.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"xbg1665702534713\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The <span class=\"keyword apiname\">uniface.View</span> object represents a view of a component that has been created by calling <span class=\"keyword apiname\">instance.createView()</span>.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"xbg1665702534713__section_w1357ab1b5b1_w1358ab1b5_w1359ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1030614e55\">\n                       \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xbg1665702534713__p_d127355e1_d127356e1_d127357e1\">For each instance of a dynamic server page, you can define multiple views of its data. For example, you can filter the data that is displayed, or provide alternate layouts for mobile and desktop-based browsers.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xbg1665702534713__p_d127358e1_d127359e1_d127360e1\">A view object is created using the <span class=\"keyword apiname\">uniface.Instance.createView</span> function, and is returned by <span class=\"keyword apiname\">uniface.Instance.getView()</span> and <span class=\"keyword apiname\">.getViews()</span>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"xbg1665702534713__section_w1360ab1b5b3_w1361ab1b5_w1362ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1030614e76\">\n                       \n Functions\n </h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"xbg1665702534713__table_d15230e1_d15231e1_d15232e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">View Functions</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"xbg1665702534713__table_d15230e1_d15231e1_d15232e1__entry__1\">\n Function\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"xbg1665702534713__table_d15230e1_d15231e1_d15232e1__entry__2\">\n Description\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xbg1665702534713__table_d15230e1_d15231e1_d15232e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rpg1665702534804.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rpg1665702534804.html\" title=\"Display the View inside its parent element as specified when the View was created (using uniface.Instance.createView).\">show()</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xbg1665702534713__table_d15230e1_d15231e1_d15232e1__entry__2\">Make the View visible inside the specified\n                        parent element. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xbg1665702534713__table_d15230e1_d15231e1_d15232e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gdf1665702534898.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gdf1665702534898.html\" title=\"Hide the View by removing it from its parent element.\">hide()</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xbg1665702534713__table_d15230e1_d15231e1_d15232e1__entry__2\">\n Hide the View. Remove it from its parent element.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xbg1665702534713__table_d15230e1_d15231e1_d15232e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"cfy1665702534987.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cfy1665702534987.html\" title=\"Delete the DSP view object.\">remove()</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xbg1665702534713__table_d15230e1_d15231e1_d15232e1__entry__2\">\n Delete the View. After this, the View object is invalid, and any attempt to call its member functions throws a <span class=\"keyword apiname\">uniface.InvalidDataObjectException</span> exception.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xbg1665702534713__table_d15230e1_d15231e1_d15232e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rmh1665702535076.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rmh1665702535076.html\" title=\"Returns true if the view is valid.\">isValid()</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xbg1665702534713__table_d15230e1_d15231e1_d15232e1__entry__2\">\n Returns true if the View is valid.\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"xbg1665702534713__note_w1363ab1b5b3b5_w1364ab1b5b3_w1365ab1b5_w1366ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> The View\n            functions are not supported for the default view, which is created by the\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">weblayout</span> ProcScript statement, not by calling\n               <span class=\"keyword apiname\">instance.createView()</span>.</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/skz1665702535167.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Multiple Views for Dynamic Server Pages</a><p>A View is an HTML layout that is displayed inside an unbound HTML element in the layout of the web page. Each instance of a dynamic server page (DSP) can have multiple views that provide different layouts for its data.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vzv1665702534087.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>createView</a><p>Creates a View of the component instance with the specified name and layout.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xlf1665702534189.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>getView()</a><p>Get the specified view of the component instance.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gjv1665702534276.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>getViews</a><p>Returns an array of uniface.View objects representing the views of a component instance.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fpa1665702539028.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>weblayout</a><p>Copies the layout of the dynamic server page instance and prepares to send it to the browser.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533626\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533626\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "uniface.View Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 14, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 The uniface.View object represents a view of a component that has been created by calling instance.createView() . Description For each instance of a dynamic server page, you can define multiple views of its data. For example, you can filter the data that is displayed, or provide alternate layouts for mobile and desktop-based browsers. A view object is created using the uniface.Instance.createView function, and is returned by uniface.Instance.getView() and .getViews() . Functions Table 1. View Functions Function Description show() Make the View visible inside the specified parent element. hide() Hide the View. Remove it from its parent element. remove() Delete the View. After this, the View object is invalid, and any attempt to call its member functions throws a uniface.InvalidDataObjectException exception. isValid() Returns true if the View is valid. Note: The View functions are not supported for the default view, which is created by the weblayout ProcScript statement, not by calling instance.createView() . Related Links Multiple Views for Dynamic Server Pages A View is an HTML layout that is displayed inside an unbound HTML element in the layout of the web page. Each instance of a dynamic server page (DSP) can have multiple views that provide different layouts for its data. createView Creates a View of the component instance with the specified name and layout. getView() Get the specified view of the component instance. getViews Returns an array of uniface.View objects representing the views of a component instance. weblayout Copies the layout of the dynamic server page instance and prepares to send it to the browser. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}